 "to stand before me."

1280
00:52:20,520 --> 00:52:22,280
 And when Latimore stood back before Henry VIII,

1281
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:25,600
 he said this, "Hugh Latimore, does thou know

1282
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:27,320
 "before whom thou art to speak this day?"

1283
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:29,560
 He, in a sense, took third person.

1284
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:31,920
 "I am to speak to the high and mighty monarch,

1285
00:52:31,920 --> 00:52:33,520
 "the king's most excellent majesty,

1286
00:52:33,520 --> 00:52:36,680
 "who can take away thy life if he offends him.

1287
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:40,080
 "Therefore, Hugh, take heed that thou speak not a word

1288
00:52:40,080 --> 00:52:41,600
 "that might displease the king.

1289
00:52:41,600 --> 00:52:44,560
 "And then consider well, Hugh, that if you do this,

1290
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:47,600
 "when you come upon this message that you're sent to give,

1291
00:52:47,600 --> 00:52:49,840
 "that the great and mighty God might give you grace,

1292
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:52,080
 "but this king surely won't give you grace.

1293
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:55,320
 "The one who beholds your ways presently,

1294
00:52:55,320 --> 00:52:57,720
 "this one who was able to kill you,

1295
00:52:57,720 --> 00:53:01,080
 "but Hugh, you stand and speak with the God

1296
00:53:01,080 --> 00:53:03,380
 "who is able not to destroy the body that that king can,

1297
00:53:03,380 --> 00:53:05,400
 "but cast the soul into hell wants you to do,

1298
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:07,920
 "and you speak forth true to him."

1299
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:09,480
 And he did that, the king went crazy.

1300
00:53:09,480 --> 00:53:12,160
 It wasn't long before Hugh Latimore found himself

1301
00:53:12,160 --> 00:53:15,680
 tied to a stake about ready to get burned with his friend.

1302
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:20,640
 And when he walked to the stake to get burned,

1303
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:24,720
 Hugh Latimore turned to his friend and he just said this.

1304
00:53:24,720 --> 00:53:29,720
 He said, "Nicholas, take heart, play the man,

1305
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:31,580
 "because we shall this day light a candle

1306
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:33,060
 "by God's grace in England,

1307
00:53:33,060 --> 00:53:35,840
 "as I trust shall never be put out."

1308
00:53:35,840 --> 00:53:41,120
 And then God's sheep was burned at the stake.

1309
00:53:41,120 --> 00:53:45,700
 And it started a revival.

1310
00:53:46,700 --> 00:53:49,820
 And it stiffened the spines of others

1311
00:53:49,820 --> 00:53:53,460
 because somebody did what the remnant should do,

1312
00:53:53,460 --> 00:53:55,540
 graciously but boldly.

1313
00:53:55,540 --> 00:53:59,860
 Look guys, I don't know where this thing is headed.

1314
00:53:59,860 --> 00:54:03,300
 I heard a guy say this one time, he said,

1315
00:54:03,300 --> 00:54:04,840
 "I think I'm gonna probably die in my shame

1316
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:07,300
 "because I'm gonna be criticized and called intolerant

1317
00:54:07,300 --> 00:54:10,400
 "and called old fashioned and out of step with the times.

1318
00:54:10,400 --> 00:54:12,900
 "I think my successor will probably die in chains,

1319
00:54:12,900 --> 00:54:15,660
 "and I think his successor will probably die in flames."

1320
00:54:16,660 --> 00:54:21,020
 But mark my word, his successor will pick up the ashes

1321
00:54:21,020 --> 00:54:24,940
 and will restore a godly generation.

1322
00:54:24,940 --> 00:54:32,500
 The remnant should be humble because it sees things

1323
00:54:32,500 --> 00:54:34,380
 that only God can let them see.

1324
00:54:34,380 --> 00:54:37,740
 The remnant should shine because they live in a way

1325
00:54:37,740 --> 00:54:39,780
 that only people who are associated with a holy God

1326
00:54:39,780 --> 00:54:43,180
 can shine, the way they date, the way they suffer,

1327
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:45,580
 the way they speak, the way they love.

1328
00:54:45,580 --> 00:54:48,100
 The remnant speaks.

1329
00:54:48,100 --> 00:54:51,500
 And the remnant stands firm because it knows

1330
00:54:51,500 --> 00:54:54,180
 that even if they're burned at the stake,

1331
00:54:54,180 --> 00:54:57,660
 to die is gain.

1332
00:54:57,660 --> 00:55:03,260
 Paul said, "It's better for you if I remain.

1333
00:55:03,260 --> 00:55:06,540
 "But if you wanna send me to glory, send me to glory.

1334
00:55:06,540 --> 00:55:09,740
 "But while I'm here, I will live for the glory of my king

1335
00:55:09,740 --> 00:55:12,180
 "who lived and died for me."

